summary: An Ordinance granting to the Covington Lumber Co., its successors and assigns, a license and permission to lay down, construct, maintain and operate a single track railway for logging purposes, with the necessary side tracks, upon over and across certain lands belonging to the City of Seattle, in the vicinity of Swan Lake, and to construct a roll-way, or roll-ways, along side of or to said lakes, and to deposit boom and haul logs therein.
